According to the [YAML spec for floating-points](http://yaml.org/type/float.html), I should be able to specify numbers using scientific notation format.  For example:

```yaml
foo: 5e-324
```

But js-yaml's `safeLoad()` method parses this as a *string* property, rather than a *number*.   The `safeDump()` method serializes floating-point numbers using scientific notation format, so it seems logical that the `safeLoad()` method should correctly de-serialize them.

```javascript
var obj1 = {foo: 5e-324};
var str = yaml.safeDump(obj1);
var obj2 = yaml.safeLoad(str);

// obj1 === {foo: 5e-324}      <--- number
// obj2 === {foo: "5e-324"}    <--- string
```

